Yeah, is there an expiry on this build, or will it keep working?

#!/bin/sh
#
# Patch for Microsoft Office 2011 Beta 5
# by Wanderer, updated for Beta 5 by Sixer
#
# Removes beta expiration
#

TARGET="/Applications/Microsoft Office 2011/Office/MicrosoftComponentPlugin.framework/Ve$
OFFSET=0xE83CE
PATCH="\xB8\x00\x00\x00\x00\xC3"

if [ -f "$TARGET" ]; then
        printf $PATCH | dd conv=notrunc of="$TARGET" seek=$OFFSET bs=1
        STATUS=$?
        if [ $STATUS -eq "0" ]; then
                echo "******************************************"
                echo "*          PATCHED SUCCESSFULLY          *"
                echo "******************************************"
        else
                echo "******************************************"
                echo "*   Problem Patching, check permissions  *"
                echo "******************************************"
        fi
else
        echo "******************************************"
        echo "*    Problem Patching, file not found    *"
        echo "******************************************"
fi

Works great! Couple of hints:
1. The main serial number is for the Beta 4; not sure why this was included. In this beta, you need to enter the individual serial number for each app (Word, Excel, etc.) and then each one works fine.
2. If you are trying to patch the expiration, there is a bug in the script posted by "sixer". Replace the TARGET line with the following:
TARGET="/Applications/Microsoft Office 2011/Office/MicrosoftComponentPlugin.framework/Versions/14/MicrosoftComponentPlugin"
That should work much better.
In the above, make sure the TARGET is a single line, not two lines as it appears in the browser.
